'''Geophilic''' means [[soil]] loving or preferring the soil.<ref>Biology-Online.org http://www.biology-online.org/dictionary/Geophilic</ref> This term is usually used when referring to certain types of fungi or molds that live in the soil.<ref>[http://www.answers.com/topic/geophilic Geophilic: Definition from Answers.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Many of these organisms are usually recovered from the soil but occasionally infect [[human]]s and [[animal]]s. They cause a marked [[Inflammation|inflammatory reaction]], which limits the spread of the [[infection]] and may lead to a spontaneous cure but may also leave [[scar]]s.<ref>The Dermatophytes - Weitzman, Irene http://cmr.asm.org/cgi/reprint/8/2/240.pdf</ref>

Can also refer to someone who loves the earth, [[sustainability]], or “green” initiatives. An individual with these tendencies may be referred to as a "geophile."

