[[File:Elektrownia wiatrowa- Nowy Tomyśl.jpg|thumb]]
The '''Nowy Tomyśl Wind Turbines''' are the tallest [[wind turbine]]s in the world.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://epoznan.pl/news-news-36935-Nowy_Tomysl_powstaly_najwyzsze_wiatraki_na_swiecie |title=Nowy Tomyśl: powstały najwyższe wiatraki na świecie! |publisher=Epoznan.pl |date=3 December 2012 |language=Polish}}</ref> They are situated in [[Paproć]], a suburb of [[Nowy Tomyśl]] in [[Poland]] and were erected in 2012. Each of these two wind turbines has a generating capacity of 2500&nbsp;kW. Both rotors have a diameter of 100 metres and are mounted on 160 metre tall free-standing [[lattice tower]]s, which are the tallest free-standing lattice towers in Poland.

The basement of each of these turbines weighs 1500 tons, the tower 350 tons and the gondola 100 tons.

